types.name: Query
types.description: Queries retrieve data from the data store.

fields.name: availableConnectorTypes
fields.description: Returns the complete list of Connector Types (type = category or vendor) available to you for install; this does not reflect which Connectors are already installed, use "connectors" for that query.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is typically used to restrict results to a specific connector type or types.

fields.name: buildings
fields.description: Buildings are subsections of sites, where each site may have multiple associated buildings. Use this query to view building specific data such as id, name and geoshape.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is typically used to restrict results to a specific building or buildings.

fields.name: calendarEvents
fields.description: Currently in development; will be used in association with Connectors that expose calendar events such as scheduled meetings.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is used to return information about a specific calendar event.

fields.name: connectorAuth
fields.description: Currently in development.

args.name: id
args.description: Provide the ID for the connector auth here.

fields.name: connectorTypes
fields.description: Currently in development.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is most often used to restrict results to a specific connector type or types.

fields.name: connectors
fields.description: Use this query to view data about the Connectors configured for the organization, including gateways.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is typically used to restrict results to a specific connector or connectors.

fields.name: floors
fields.description: Floors are subsections of buildings, typically identified numerically like "floor1". Use this query to view floor specific data such as id, name or geoshape.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is typically used to restrict results to a specific floor or floors.

fields.name: gateways
fields.description: Provides details about the gateways associated with the organization, such as id or provisioning/active status.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is typically used to restrict results to a specific gateway or gateways.

fields.name: grants
fields.description: Currently in development; will be used to list details about grants that provide access rights to parties outside the organization (like granting building tenants the right to view data about their spaces)

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is typically used to restrict results to a specific grant or grants.

fields.name: invites
fields.description: Invites are used to add additional users to the org. Use this query to return the list of user invites created by your org, including those that were ACCEPTED or still PENDING.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter typically used to restrict results to a specific invite or invites.

fields.name: liveQueries
fields.description: Live queries are GraphQL queries created once and then remain active, monitoring for changes perpetually for easy retrieval. Typically paired with a webhook to get proactive notificiations of changes pushed to an endpoint.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter typically used to restrict results to a specific live query or queries.

fields.name: me
fields.description: Use this query to view data about the user associated with the token, such as name or id.

fields.name: organization
fields.description: Use this query to view data about the organization associated with the the token, such as name or id.

fields.name: people
fields.description: Currently in development and will be used in with connectors that expose information about individuals, such as calendar events.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is used to return information about a specific person.

fields.name: points
fields.description: A particular output at a particular time, like on/off for a device like a light. For more complex devices like a thermostat, points could be the ambient temperature in the room, what temperature is set, is the thermostat set to heat or set to cool.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is typically used to restrict results to a specific point or points.

fields.name: productBundleSubscriptions
fields.description: For internal use only.

fields.name: sites
fields.description: Sites are the top level place - they contain buildings, which contain floors, which contain spaces. Use this query to view site specific data such as id, name or geoshape.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is typically used to restrict results to a specific site or sites.

fields.name: spaces
fields.description: Spaces are subsections of a floor, such as an office or a breakroom. Use this query to view space specific data such as id, name or geoshape.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is typically used to restrict results to a specific space or spaces.

fields.name: things
fields.description: All the devices in your places - HVAC systems, security systems, lighting, badge readers, elevators and similar.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is most often used torestrict results to a specific thing or things.

fields.name: tokens
fields.description: This will return information about the tokens in your account, or if you're an admin, you can look at tokens for other users. Note this will not return the actual Personal Access Token, only the token record id and data like the name and scopes.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is typically used to restrict results to a specific token or tokens.

fields.name: units
fields.description: Predefined / global list containing units of measurement for point data, such as "Degrees". Used for timeseries data comprehension, i.e. series data for a point shows "65", units helps you understand that means 65 degrees.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is typically used to restrict results to a specific unit or units.

fields.name: users
fields.description: If you're an admin, use this query to retrieve data about users. If you're a non-admin user, you can review the listed data about yourself.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is typically used to restrict results to a specific user or users.

fields.name: webhookTargets
fields.description: Used to return data about webhook targets created by org admins.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is used to return information about a specific webhook.

types.name: String
types.description: The `String` scalar type represents textual data, represented as UTF-8 character sequences. The String type is most often used by GraphQL to represent free-form human-readable text.

types.name: DateTime
types.description: An RFC-3339 compliant DateTime Scalar

types.name: IDFilterExpressionInput
types.description: Used as the input control for the filter, determining if you're looking for a single result or multiple results.

inputFields.name: eq
inputFields.description: Use this field to filter for a single, specific ID.

inputFields.name: in
inputFields.description: Use this field to return results for all IDs present in a set, like [ID12345, ID67890].

types.name: PointFilter
types.description: Contains the input values needed to filter point queries.

inputFields.name: and
inputFields.description: Used to combine multiple filter criteria.

inputFields.name: id
inputFields.description: Used to filter for a specific ID or IDs (refer to IDFilterExpressionInput for input options).

inputFields.name: not
inputFields.description: Used to omit a specific result or results from the response.

inputFields.name: or
inputFields.description: Used to return results that match at least one of the defined criteria.

inputFields.name: type
inputFields.description: Used to filter on a class or subclass of the point, like "Alarm" and "TemperatureAlarm".

types.name: Boolean
types.description: The `Boolean` scalar type represents `true` or `false`.

types.name: Point
types.description: Contains the details about the point, such as a thermostat setpoint.

fields.name: aggregation
fields.description: Time series data gathered together to return a new value, such as an average temperature across a set time pe or a min or max value.

args.name: endTime
args.description: The ending timestamp for the aggregated series data.

args.name: period
args.description: The interval of time to use for the aggregation. Supports DAY, HOUR and MINUTE.

args.name: startTime
args.description: The starting timestamp for the aggregated series data.

fields.name: dateCreated
fields.description: This timestamp represents the date the point was created.

fields.name: dateUpdated
fields.description: This timestamp represents that date the point was last updated.

fields.name: description
fields.description: The description of the point, like "Cooling Temperature Setpoint".

fields.name: exactType
fields.description: This is the most specific type available for the point, i.e. where 'type' may return a list like [Point, Alarm, TemperatureAlarm, HighTemperatureAlarm], exactType will return just HighTemperatureAlarm.

fields.name: id
fields.description: The unique ID of the point.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name assigned to the point.

fields.name: series
fields.description: Time series data for the point, such as what the air temperature setpoint was for a VAV, limited by a defined start and end time.

args.name: endTime
args.description: The ending timestamp for the series data.

args.name: latest
args.description: If set to 'true', will return the last timeseries value we have for the point.

args.name: startTime
args.description: The starting timestamp for the series data.

fields.name: stateTexts
fields.description: Ordered list of additional descriptive data to help explain float values like 0.0, 1.0 and 2.0.

fields.name: type
fields.description: The class or subclass of the point, like "Alarm" and "TemperatureAlarm".

fields.name: unit
fields.description: The unit of measurement associated with this point, such as "Degrees".

types.name: Int
types.description: The `Int` scalar type represents non-fractional signed whole numeric values. Int can represent values between -(2^31) and 2^31 - 1.

types.name: Float
types.description: The `Float` scalar type represents signed double-precision fractional values as specified by [IEEE 754](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IEEE_floating_point).

types.name: GeoJSON
types.description: Geodata in JSON format

types.name: Building
types.description: Contains all the details of a building.

fields.name: address
fields.description: The address of a building, contains fields that support international addresses.

fields.name: connectors
fields.description: Any connectors configured for a building will be listed here.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is most often used to restrict results to a specific connector or connectors.

fields.name: dateCreated
fields.description: This timestamp represents the date the building was created.

fields.name: dateUpdated
fields.description: This timestamp represents that date the building was last updated.

fields.name: description
fields.description: The description of a building; often left blank, especially if the building name is already descriptive.

fields.name: exactType
fields.description: The exactType is the most granular Brick Schema Location type defined for this building.

fields.name: floors
fields.description: All the floors present in a building will be listed here.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is most often used to restrict results to a specific floor or floors.

fields.name: hasPoint
fields.description: In some limited scenarios, a point may be associated with a building as opposed to a thing, like a building electrical meter. Those details will be provided here.

fields.name: id
fields.description: The unique ID of a building.

fields.name: isLocationOf
fields.description: Superset of anything that could be in a building - a thing, a person, a meeting (people and meetings currently in development).

fields.name: isPartOf
fields.description: This contains the next level up in the place hierarchy; for a building, this will contain site information.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of a building; often just the street address.

fields.name: points
fields.description: Any of the points available inside a building will be listed here.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is most often used to restrict results to a specific point or points.

fields.name: sites
fields.description: The site associated with a building.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is most often used to restrict results to a specific site or sites.

fields.name: things
fields.description: All the things associated with a building, or any floor or space in the building, will show here.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is most often used to restrict results to a specific thing or things.

fields.name: type
fields.description: Type includes all possible hierarchal types for the building, such as "Place" and "Building".

types.name: Place
types.description: Contains all the details of any places associated with a particular thing, such as a space or a floor.

fields.name: id
fields.description: The unique ID of the place.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of the place.

fields.name: things
fields.description: Contains the complete list of things associated with the place.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is most often used to restrict results to a specific thing or things.

types.name: Person
types.description: Contains the details about a individual detected in the data from a building, such as a conference room booking.

fields.name: emails
fields.description: Any emails associated with the individual.

fields.name: familyName
fields.description: Surname or last name of the individual.

fields.name: givenName
fields.description: Personal name or first name of the individual.

fields.name: id
fields.description: The unique ID of the individual.

types.name: ThingFilter
types.description: Contains the input values needed to filter thing queries.

inputFields.name: and
inputFields.description: Used to combine multiple filter criteria.

inputFields.name: id
inputFields.description: Used to filter for a specific ID or IDs (refer to IDFilterExpressionInput for input options).

inputFields.name: not
inputFields.description: Used to omit a specific result or results from the response.

inputFields.name: or
inputFields.description: Used to return results that match at least one of the defined criteria.

inputFields.name: type
inputFields.description: Used to filter on a specific class or subclass of a thing, like HVAC and AHU.

types.name: Thing
types.description: Contains the details about a thing.

fields.name: description
fields.description: The description of a thing, like Rooftop Air Handler.

fields.name: exactType
fields.description: This is the most specific type available for a thing, i.e. where 'type' may return a list like [Device, HVAC, Damper], exactType will return just Damper.

fields.name: firmwareVersion
fields.description: This is primarily a Building Automation System field; when available, it will provide the firmware version for a device.

fields.name: geoshape
fields.description: The geographic shape of a thing, represented by latitude/longitude coordinate pairs.

fields.name: hasLocation
fields.description: This represents the location of a thing, such as a space name.

fields.name: hasPart
fields.description: If a thing has any additional parts, like a VAV with a damper, the damper will be referenced here.

fields.name: id
fields.description: The unique ID of a thing.

fields.name: isPartOf
fields.description: If a thing is 'a part of' a different device, like a damper that's part of a VAV, the VAV will be referenced here.

fields.name: model
fields.description: If available, the model - along with manufacturer information - of a thing will be outlined here.
fields.deprecationReason: No longer supported. Scheduled for removal on 02/21/2024. Use hasDeviceModel and manufacturedBy query as an alternative.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of a thing, usually abbreviations of the thing's description along with location details and/or BAS information.

fields.name: organization
fields.description: The organization a thing belongs to; this field will be restricted by access rights.

fields.name: places
fields.description: The details of the place(s) where a thing is located, such as a specific building, floor, or space.

fields.name: points
fields.description: A list of points associated with a thing, such as a temperature setting for a thermostat. Not all things will have points.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is most often used to restrict results to a specific point or points.

fields.name: type
fields.description: The class or subclass of a thing, like HVAC and AHU.

types.name: Floor
types.description: Contains the details about the floor.

fields.name: building
fields.description: Contains the details of the building where the floor is present.

fields.name: connectors
fields.description: Any connectors configured for the floor will be listed here.

args.name: filter
args.description: This is the filter for the connectors field, most often used to restrict results to a specific connector or connectors.

fields.name: dateCreated
fields.description: This timestamp represents the date the floor was created.

fields.name: dateUpdated
fields.description: This timestamp represents that date the floor was last updated.

fields.name: description
fields.description: The description of the floor; often left blank, especially if the floor name is already descriptive.

fields.name: geoshape
fields.description: The geographic shape of the floor, represented by latitude/longitude coordinate pairs.

fields.name: hasPart
fields.description: Lists the spaces on the floor - spaces are "part of" a floor.

fields.name: id
fields.description: The unique ID of the floor.

fields.name: isPartOf
fields.description: This contains the next level up in the place hierarchy; for a floor, this will contain building information.

fields.name: level
fields.description: This is the floor level represented numerically. Starting at 0 for ground floor, with basement levels below ground floor identified as negative numbers.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of the floor, typically just a number or "floor1", "floor2".

fields.name: points
fields.description: Any of the points available on the floor will be listed here.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is most often used to restrict results to a specific point or points.

fields.name: spaces
fields.description: All the spaces present on the floor will be listed here.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is most often used to restrict results to a specific space or spaces.

fields.name: things
fields.description: All the things associated with the floor, or any spaces on the floor, will show here.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is most often used to restrict results to a specific thing or things.

fields.name: type
fields.description: Type includes all possible hierarchal types for the building, such as "Place" and "Floor".

fields.name: zones
fields.description: Currently in development; will show all the zones associated with the floor.

args.name: filter
args.description: This filter is most often used to restrict results to a specific zone or zones.

types.name: ConnectorFilterInput
types.description: Contains the input values needed to filter Connector queries.

inputFields.name: connectorTypeId
inputFields.description: Used if you want to filter by a connectorType instead of a specific Connector installation.

inputFields.name: id
inputFields.description: Used to filter for a specific ID or IDs (refer to IDFilterExpressionInput for input options).

types.name: ConnectorStateInput
types.description: Current state of the Connector.

enumValues.name: ACTIVE
enumValues.description: Connector is up and running, retrieving data from the device vendor.

enumValues.name: CONNECTOR_STATE_UNSPECIFIED
enumValues.description: Connector state cannot be identified, contact support@mapped.com for help.

enumValues.name: DELETED
enumValues.description: Connector was deleted, displays for audit purposes.

enumValues.name: DELETING
enumValues.description: Transient state, displayed while Connector is in process of deletion.

enumValues.name: ERROR_GENERAL
enumValues.description: Connector is in an error state, contact support@mapped.com for help.

enumValues.name: STOPPED
enumValues.description: Connector is stopped, no longer retrieving data from the device vendor, but still exists and can be restarted.

enumValues.name: STOPPING
enumValues.description: Transient state, displayed while Connector is in process of stopping.

types.name: Connector
types.description: Contains the details about a Connector.

fields.name: config
fields.description: Any settings required in order to create a Connector will be provided here.

fields.name: configHash
fields.description: Random string that identifies the current Connector configuration; if you need to update the configuration, you will need to include the current configHash value in the mutation request.

fields.name: connectorType
fields.description: The type/category/vendor of a Connector, such as "Weather" or "Butlr".

fields.name: connectorTypeId
fields.description: The unique id of the connector type.

fields.name: created
fields.description: Timestamp for the Connector's creation.

fields.name: id
fields.description: The unique id of a Connector.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of a Connector you provided when setting it up for your org.

fields.name: organization
fields.description: Contains the details about the organization associated with this Connector.

fields.name: points
fields.description: Lists all the points returned by the Connector.

fields.name: state
fields.description: Lists the state of a Connector, such as ACTIVE or STOPPED.

fields.name: stateDetails
fields.description: Currently provides additional information about a Connector in an ERROR_GENERAL state.

fields.name: things
fields.description: Lists all the things returned by the Connector.

fields.name: updated
fields.description: Timestamp when a connector was last updated.

fields.name: workflowId
fields.description: This is an internal-only field; the value(s) included in this field may be requested by support for troubleshooting purposes, but otherwise holds no value for external developers.

types.name: Gateway
types.description: Contains the details about the gateway.

fields.name: active
fields.description: If the gateway is in an active state, this will contain the last seen time value.

fields.name: assignment
fields.description: Contains the gateway place assignment details, including place IDs and system types.

fields.name: firstBoot
fields.description: This contains the timestamp for the gateway's first boot.

fields.name: gatewayId
fields.description: The unique ID of the gateway.

fields.name: organization
fields.description: Contains the details about the organization associated with this gateway.

fields.name: provisioning
fields.description: Contains the timestamp for the gateway's initial provisioning to the organization.

fields.name: registration
fields.description: Contains gateway registration details, including serial number and IMEI information.

fields.name: rma
fields.description: If the gateway needs to be returned, this will contain details like the RMA reason along with any explanatory notes.

fields.name: shipping
fields.description: If the gateway is currently in a SHIPPED state, details about the shipment will show here, including carrier and tracking number.

fields.name: state
fields.description: The current state of the gateway - many states are transitory, like FIRST_BOOT; the more common states will be ACTIVE, ASSIGNED, PROVISIONING and SHIPPED as those exist for longer windows.

fields.name: stateTime
fields.description: Timestamp for the start of the current state.

fields.name: suspension
fields.description: If the gateway was suspended, this will contain details like the suspension reason along with any explanatory notes.

fields.name: termination
fields.description: If the gateway was terminated, this will contain details like the suspension reason along with any explanatory notes. This differs from suspenson as the gateway cannot be returned to active once terminated.

types.name: __Schema
types.description: A GraphQL Schema defines the capabilities of a GraphQL server. It exposes all available types and directives on the server, as well as the entry points for query, mutation, and subscription operations.

fields.name: types
fields.description: A list of all types supported by this server.

fields.name: queryType
fields.description: The type that query operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: mutationType
fields.description: If this server supports mutation, the type that mutation operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: subscriptionType
fields.description: If this server support subscription, the type that subscription operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: directives
fields.description: A list of all directives supported by this server.

types.name: __Type
types.description:
The fundamental unit of any GraphQL Schema is the type. There are many kinds of types in GraphQL as represented by the `__TypeKind` enum.

Depending on the kind of a type, certain fields describe information about that type. Scalar types provide no information beyond a name and description, while Enum types provide their values. Object and Interface types provide the fields they describe. Abstract types, Union and Interface, provide the Object types possible at runtime. List and NonNull types compose other types.

types.name: __TypeKind
types.description: An enum describing what kind of type a given `__Type` is.

enumValues.name: SCALAR
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a scalar.

enumValues.name: OBJECT

types.name: __Field
types.description: Object and Interface types are described by a list of Fields, each of which has a name, potentially a list of arguments, and a return type.

types.name: __InputValue
types.description: Arguments provided to Fields or Directives and the input fields of an InputObject are represented as Input Values which describe their type and optionally a default value.

fields.name: defaultValue
fields.description: A GraphQL-formatted string representing the default value for this input value.

types.name: __EnumValue
types.description: One possible value for a given Enum. Enum values are unique values, not a placeholder for a string or numeric value. However an Enum value is returned in a JSON response as a string.

types.name: __Directive
types.description:
A Directive provides a way to describe alternate runtime execution and type validation behavior in a GraphQL document.

In some cases, you need to provide options to alter GraphQL's execution behavior in ways field arguments will not suffice, such as conditionally including or skipping a field. Directives provide this by describing additional information to the executor.

types.name: __DirectiveLocation
types.description: A Directive can be adjacent to many parts of the GraphQL language, a __DirectiveLocation describes one such possible adjacencies.

directives.description: The GRPC directive stores information about the GRPC call. If the field is marked with a directive, then the result will be obtained from the result of the GRPC call.
